&lt;section class=&quot;block the-good&quot;&gt;
	&lt;h4&gt;The good...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Minneapolis nominated for Nobel Peace Prize &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newsweek.com/minneapolis-nominated-nobel-peace-prize-anti-ice-protests-11457239&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;

    &lt;a href=&quot;/images/QaYsOMu3V0-500.webp&quot; class=&quot;lightbox-link&quot; aria-haspopup=&quot;dialog&quot; style=&quot;cursor:zoom-in&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img class=&quot;img-lightbox&quot; alt=&quot;Nobel Peace Prize&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/QaYsOMu3V0-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;500&quot; height=&quot;492&quot; srcset=&quot;/images/QaYsOMu3V0-200.webp 200w, /images/QaYsOMu3V0-500.webp 500w&quot; sizes=&quot;200px&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Nobel Peace Prize Medal.&lt;/b&gt; Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:Jonathunder&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Jonathunder&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Nobel_Prize.png&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;No, that title is not a typo. Nor is it click-bait. It&#39;s actually true. The Nobel Peace Price is usually given to individuals  and sometimes to organizations that promote peace. But this year, Minneapolis, Minnesota, and its residents have collectively been nominated for the 2026 Nobel Peace Prize.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Nominations were open until January 31, and will be reviewed by the Norwegian Nobel Committee through September. The winner will be announced in October, and the aware ceremony will be held in December.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;blockquote&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;[Minneapolis] has met and exceeded the committee&#39;s standard of promoting democracy and human rights, and work aimed at creating a better organized and more peaceful world.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;[The people of Minneapolis have] suffered countless abuses, including harassment, detention, deportation, and injury.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;[In response to these incidents, Minneapolis leaders called for] nonviolent protest, in accordance with the U.S. Constitution’s promise that Americans have a right to assemble and petition for the redress of grievances.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;figcaption class=&quot;blockquote-footer&quot;&gt;Letter to the Norwegian Nobel Committee from &lt;i&gt;The Nation&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
		&lt;/blockquote&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Related Links:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;ul class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(Newsweek) Minneapolis nominated for Nobel Peace Prize after anti-ICE protests&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thenation.com/article/activism/the-nation-nominates-minneapolis-for-the-nobel-peace-prize/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(The Nation) &lt;i&gt;The Nation&lt;/i&gt; nominates Minneapolis for the Nobel Peace Prize&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;hr style=&quot;clear:both&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Alex Pretti&#39;s killers identified &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.propublica.org/article/alex-pretti-shooting-cbp-agents-identified-jesus-ochoa-raymundo-gutierrez&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;

    &lt;a href=&quot;/images/jzfp4-4Dpe-800.webp&quot; class=&quot;lightbox-link&quot; aria-haspopup=&quot;dialog&quot; style=&quot;cursor:zoom-in&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img class=&quot;img-lightbox&quot; alt=&quot;Alex Pretti Memorial&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/jzfp4-4Dpe-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;600&quot; srcset=&quot;/images/jzfp4-4Dpe-200.webp 200w, /images/jzfp4-4Dpe-800.webp 800w&quot; sizes=&quot;200px&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Memorial for Alex Pretti.&lt;/b&gt; Image by Nvss132 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Pretti_memorial_and_candles.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/deed.en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Creative Commons CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The two agents who shot Alex Pretti in the streets of Minneapolis have been identified: Jesus Ochoa and Raymundo Gutierrez.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Both were employed by Customs and Border Protection and assigned to Operation Metro Surge, the Trump regime&#39;s unprecedented deployment of armed and masked agents sent to sow terror into the hearts and minds of the American public. The move has led to massive protests in Minneapolis and around the country.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Department of Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem spread blatant lies about the execution of Pretti immediately after the incident, along with other representatives of the Trump regime. The government has tried to interfere with any investigation into the killing, despite the fact that videos of the event are readily available to the public that clearly expose the lies of the regime.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;These are the exact same tactics the regime tried to unsuccessfully employ after Renee Good was killed by Jonathan Ross just a few weeks earlier. But every time their lies are exposed, their support base weakens, their power is threatened, and public outrage grows. It remains to be seen whether the public outcry will ultimately lead to the toppling of the regime, or if they will be able to escalate their terror tactics enough to suppress any effective opposition to the regime&#39;s power.&lt;/p&gt;
