&lt;section class=&quot;block the-bad&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The bad...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Kennedy Center closing after Trump&#39;s failed takeover &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2026/feb/01/kennedy-center-dc-closed-trump&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;

    &lt;a href=&quot;/images/sx-RJndppy-800.webp&quot; class=&quot;lightbox-link&quot; aria-haspopup=&quot;dialog&quot; style=&quot;cursor:zoom-in&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img class=&quot;img-lightbox&quot; alt=&quot;Kennedy Center, 2010&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/sx-RJndppy-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;464&quot; srcset=&quot;/images/sx-RJndppy-200.webp 200w, /images/sx-RJndppy-800.webp 800w&quot; sizes=&quot;200px&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;The John F. Kennedy Memorial Center for the Performing Arts.&lt;/b&gt; Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Tom&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Tom&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Kennedy_Center_seen_from_the_Potomac_River,_June_2010.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons.&lt;/a&gt; Licensed under the &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/deed.en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported license&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Donny 2-Dolls thinks he&#39;s a brilliant businessman, but his lifelong habit of destroying the businesses he runs shows us otherwise. And his string of failed businesses continues even during his second term as president.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Last year, Trump took over control of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts in Washington D.C. and renamed it to the &quot;The Donald Trump and the John F. Kennedy Memorial Center for the Performing Arts.&quot; The name itself is laughable due to the grammatical errors in the new name (It should read &quot;The Donald Trump and John F. Kennedy...&quot;) and the fact that the term &quot;memorial&quot; should only be used when the namesake is deceased.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;What&#39;s even more laughable is the utter failure Donny 2-Dolls has made of the Center. Once a world-class venue for the performing arts, under Trump&#39;s leadership, the Kennedy Center has seen the lowest ticket sales in years, and a wave a cancellations of scheduled events. Under Trump&#39;s business leadership, the Kennedy Center can no longer remain in operation, and will close its doors for &quot;approximately&quot; two years.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Trump is claiming that the closure is to &quot;renovate&quot; the facility, but the timing is certainly questionable. Under this plan, the center will be closed until some time in 2028, and we can pretty well assume that it will remain closed until after the 2028 elections. Whether or not it reopens will no doubt depend on who wins that election.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Related Links:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;ul class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2026/feb/01/kennedy-center-dc-closed-trump&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(The Guardian) Kennedy Center will halt entertainment operations for two years, Trump says&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;hr style=&quot;clear:both&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;

&lt;section class=&quot;block the-ugly&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The ugly...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Trump announces plans for the federal government to take control of elections &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ms.now/news/trump-suggests-federal-control-of-elections-in-some-areas&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Donny 2-Dolls has been floating the idea of having Republicans &quot;take over&quot; election administration in &quot;some areas&quot; of the country.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The Constitution is very clear that elections are to be held by states without federal interference. Because of this, the president&#39;s announcements should raise alarm for anyone who believes in the rule of law and the validity of the Constitution of the Untied States of America.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Trump is claiming, without evidence (as always), that elections are &quot;unbelievably corrupt&quot; in &quot;some areas.&quot; There is no credible evidence of widespread fraud in this country&#39;s elections, and these claims are nothing more than blatant lies. FBI agents raided the Fulton County elections office in Georgia last week and took possession of official voter records from 2020, and will soon be making additional false claims that they have &quot;discovered&quot; fraud in these records, and will use this falsified evidence to claim that election fraud is a credible threat and that they have to nationalize the elections in order to ensure that their party &quot;wins&quot; the 2026 midterms.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;One thing is absolutely clear: The threats to our elections are indications that the Trump regime knows that they will lose representatives in Congress in the 2026 mid-term elections, and they are going everything in their power to try to prevent a free and fair election this year. The video below is from the weekly &lt;i&gt;What&#39;s the Plan&lt;/i&gt; discussion hosted by &lt;i&gt;Indivisible&lt;/i&gt; co-executive directors Leah Greenberg and Ezra Levin. It&#39;s an hour-long video, but if you don&#39;t have time to watch the whole thing, watch the video from where it starts (5:03) until 8:53. Leah summarizes the regime&#39;s strategy and outlines how we can best fight against it.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;div style=&quot;text-align:center&quot;&gt;
			&lt;iframe width=&quot;560&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/p-SLMw-yOkE?si=QeUmNxh_qVynpyKG&amp;amp;start=303&quot; title=&quot;YouTube video player&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&quot; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
		&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;blockquote&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;They are losing, so they are going to try to steal the election.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;They are going to fail, because we&#39;re going to stop them.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;figcaption class=&quot;blockquote-footer&quot;&gt;Leah Greenberg, Co-Executive Director, Indivisible&lt;/figcaption&gt;
		&lt;/blockquote&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Related Links:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;ul class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ms.now/news/trump-suggests-federal-control-of-elections-in-some-areas&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(MS Now) Trump suggest federal control of elections in &quot;some aread&quot;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p-SLMw-yOkE&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(YouTube-Indivisible) 2.6.26 What&#39;s the Plan? A weekly discussion with Leah and Ezra&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://robertreich.substack.com/p/could-trump-really-take-over-the&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(Substack-Robert Reich) Could Trump really &quot;take over&quot; the midterm elections?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
