&lt;section&gt;
    &lt;p class=&quot;tangerine&quot; style=&quot;text-align:center;font-size:4em;padding:1.2rem 0px;&quot;&gt;Impeach. Convict. Remove.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Recap of this week in the revolution: Nationwide protests demand ICE out of our cities. Trump regime targets journalists to silence free press. FBI seizes 2020 voter records in Georgia. Another (partial) government shutdown begins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;

&lt;section class=&quot;block the-good&quot;&gt;
	&lt;h4&gt;The good...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Protests expand, closing schools and businesses to oppose Trump regime &lt;a href=&quot;https://apnews.com/article/immigration-protests-64fd52ba5283e8f56c57dddb1c3a3852&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;

    &lt;a href=&quot;/images/ugs6XUMOS5-800.webp&quot; class=&quot;lightbox-link&quot; aria-haspopup=&quot;dialog&quot; style=&quot;cursor:zoom-in&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img class=&quot;img-lightbox&quot; alt=&quot;protestors holding sign reading &#39;Minnesota shut it down! The people have the power to stop ICE terror!&#39;&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/ugs6XUMOS5-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;533&quot; srcset=&quot;/images/ugs6XUMOS5-200.webp 200w, /images/ugs6XUMOS5-800.webp 800w&quot; sizes=&quot;200px&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.flickr.com/photos/44550450@N04/55069629476/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Fibonacci Blue&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Protest_against_ICE_in_downtown_Minneapolis_-_The_People_Have_the_Power_to_Stop_ICE_Terror.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons.&lt;/a&gt; Licensed under the &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/deed.en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 4.0 International license&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Nationwide protests erupt over the brutal slayings of Alex Pretti and Renee Good by ICE agents in Minneapolis as violence against civilians continues to escalate. On Friday, Americans around the country took to the streets again to protest the Trump regime&#39;s fascist takeover of this country. Schools and businesses in several states have closed in a grass-roots general strike intended to shut down the economy.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;These protests have been organized primarily in response to ICE violence in Minnesota, but across the country, dissatisfaction with the Trump regime&#39;s policies continues to grow. Another &quot;No Kings&quot; protest is planned for Saturday, March 28. The last &quot;No Kings&quot; protest was the largest single day of protest in the history of the United States, and it is expected that the protest on March 28 will be even larger.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;For many people, these protests feel like they are not working as the Trump regime continues to abuse its power and further demolish our democratic institutions and deny us our constitutional rights. But it&#39;s vitally important that we keep up the momentum and continue to organize and let the world know that we do not accept the current state of affairs. This is not the United States of America that any of us want to live in. So we must stay the course. Stay angry, stay loud, and make your voice heard at every opportunity. We&#39;re all afraid, we&#39;re all tired, and we&#39;re all feeling a bit hopeless. And that&#39;s exactly what the regime wants. They want to wear us down, to make us feel like nothing will ever change. They want us to accept what they are doing as the new normal. No matter what happens, we can never allow our opposition to be silenced. Find a protest, find a group, take a stand, and let the world know that you stand for liberty and justice for all.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Related Links:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;ul class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://apnews.com/article/immigration-protests-64fd52ba5283e8f56c57dddb1c3a3852&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(AP) Protesters close schools and stores during a nationwide strike against Trump&#39;s immigration policies&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;hr style=&quot;clear:both&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;

&lt;section class=&quot;block the-bad&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The bad...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Trump regime arrests journalists to intimidate the free press &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/law/2026/jan/30/press-freedom-journalist-arrests-ice-don-lemon&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;

    &lt;a href=&quot;/images/GtRK1V9I41-200.webp&quot; class=&quot;lightbox-link&quot; aria-haspopup=&quot;dialog&quot; style=&quot;cursor:zoom-in&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img class=&quot;img-lightbox&quot; alt=&quot;1958 US postage stamp: Freedom of the Press&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/GtRK1V9I41-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;307&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The Trump regime has arrested four independent journalists after they covered an anti-ICE protest in Minnesota: Don Lemon, Trahern Jeen Crews, Georgia Fort, and Jamael Lydell Lundy. These arrests were made despite the fact that multiple judges refused to approve the baseless arrest warrants. These reporters were exercising their right to report on matters of public interest, which is a fundamental pillar of a free press. The arrests are a clear indication that the Trump regime is attempting to intimidate and silence journalists who are doing their jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Civil rights activists are outraged by this blatant attempt to silence the press. Reverend Al Sharpton accused the Trump regime of taking a &quot;sledge hammer [to] the knees of the First Amendment.&quot; Lemon and Fort are both independent journalists, Crews is the co-founder of Black Lives Matter Minnesota and former candidate for mayor and state representative, and Lundy is a candidate for Minnesota Senate District 65.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The journalists were covering a peaceful protest at Cities Church in Minneapolis, Minnesota. Demonstrators disrupted a church service earlier this month because one of the staff members is a field office director for ICE. Protesters were there to point out the hypocrisy of a church that claims to follow the teachings of Jesus, the Prince of Peace, while openly supporting the ever-increasing violence of ICE in particular and the Trump regime in general.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;blockquote&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;As journalists, our first obligation is to bear witness and to inform. When those obligations are met with detention or prosecution instead of protection, we must ask: &#39;What message are we sending about who gets to report and who gets silenced?&#39;&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;figcaption class=&quot;blockquote-footer&quot;&gt;Errin Haines, &lt;i&gt;President of National Association of Black Journalists&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
        &lt;/blockquote&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Related Links:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;ul class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/law/2026/jan/30/press-freedom-journalist-arrests-ice-don-lemon&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(The Guardian) press freedom groups denounce arrests of two journalists including Don Lemon after Minnesota anti-ICE protest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pbs.org/newshour/politics/trump-administration-charges-don-lemon-with-federal-civil-rights-crimes-related-to-anti-ice-church-protest&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(PBS) Trump administration charges Don Lemon with federal civil rights crimes related to anti-ICE church protest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
