            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;50,000 people gather outdoors in -10&amp;deg;F weather to let the Trump regime know their ICE-stapo is not welcome on American soil&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;On January 23, temperatures in Minneapolis dropped to -10&amp;deg;F with wind chills reaching -20&amp;deg;F. Under normal circumstances, most people in the area would stay indoors, trying to keep warm. But these are not normal circumstances, and tens of thousands of Minnesotans filled the streets to protest the Trump regime&#39;s reign of terror and to demand the ICE-stapo agents who are threatening their very lives leave their state for good.&lt;/p&gt;
